{"source_key":"sha256-c8597aca71664a84bdd657ea13dadbd3","record_index":480,"record_hash":"sha256:2b88ae91377db5345662eac9f9bb94d92bf929fb99fa4f64801c89cb983acb3c","timestamp":"2026-05-20T01:43:18.508Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: 60c6b2\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 1814\nOutput:\n## Turn Data\n\nA turn needs an ID. The exact key shape is open, but the ID should be stable\nenough for idempotent repeated capture. Given a turn, it should be possible to\nfind the transcript records that were newly observed in that turn.\n\nTurn identity should be derived from capture content, not from time or provider\nturn ids:\n\n```text\nturn-key = sha256-hex16(session_key + NUL + source_key + NUL + ordered_new_record_hashes)\n```\n\nThat makes the newly accepted transcript records the identity of what this\ncapture observed. Capture timestamp and environment snapshot are turn\nattributes, not identity. This also makes retries easier: the same accepted\nrecord set maps to the same turn key.\n\nProvider-native turn identifiers should not define the durable `turn-key`.\nProviders may omit them, define turns differently, expose private/raw ids, or\ninclude many provider turns inside one first-time backfill capture. If present,\nthey can be stored as optional record-level grouping metadata, preferably as a\nsafe provider turn key rather than a raw provider id.\n\nMinimum useful fields:\n\n- turn id\n- session key\n- source key\n- capture timestamp\n- transcript record membership, probably by record hash and/or source record\n  index\n- optional provider turn key on transcript records, for grouping/display only\n- previous turn reference, when there is a previous capture turn in the same\n  session\n- environment snapshot\n\nThe record membership matters because `but-agentlog` already deduplicates\nrecords. Without turn membership, repeated hook capture preserves the transcript\nbut erases the boundaries between capture invocations.\n\nThe model should distinguish:\n\n- **capture turn:** a stop-hook capture observation with new transcript records\n  and a repository environment snapshot\n- **provider turn:** a provider-native conversation grouping, such as a user\n  prompt and the resulting assistant/tool activity\n\nCapture turns are the durable a\n[TRUNCATED]\nfalse\n}\n```\n\nCommit file lists should use the same pattern:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"files\": [\"src/foo.rs\", \"Cargo.toml\"],\n  \"file_count\": 2,\n  \"files_truncated\": false\n}\n```\n\nIf a list exceeds the cap, store the first capped set in deterministic sorted\norder plus the total count and `*_truncated = true`. Path hashes can be added\nlater if matching beyond the cap becomes necessary, but they should not be part\nof the first shape.\n\nDo not store commit message summaries in the turn snapshot. Commit subjects can\nbe read from Git by `commit_id` when a UI needs them, and they are not useful\nassociation evidence.\n\nConcrete turn detail example:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"schema\": \"gitbutler.agent-session-turn.v1\",\n  \"turn_key\": \"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\n  \"session_key\": \"sha256-1122334455667788\",\n  \"source_key\": \"sha256-9988776655443322\",\n  \"previous_turn_key\": \"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\n  \"captured_at\": \"2026-05-20T18:42:11.123Z\",\n  \"records\": [\n    {\n      \"source_key\": \"sha256-9988776655443322\",\n      \"record_index\": 42,\n      \"record_hash\": \"sha256:abc123...\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"environment\": {\n    \"snapshot_status\": \"complete\",\n    \"worktree\": {\n      \"files\": [\n        \"crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs\",\n        \"crates/but-agentlog/src/capture.rs\"\n      ],\n      \"file_count\": 2,\n      \"files_truncated\": false\n    },\n    \"stacks\": [\n      {\n        \"stack_id\": \"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\n        \"branches\": [\n          {\n            \"name\": \"agentlog-turns\",\n            \"re